    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.001G29/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 20.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to Mr. Innes’s note of November 28
                    last informing you of the date of the King’s coronation, and inviting a
                    representative of the President of the United States to attend the ceremony, I
                    have the honor, under instruction from His Majesty’s principal secretary of
                    state for foreign affairs, to inform you that the King has decided that the
                    State visits are to commence on Monday the 19th of June next and terminate on
                    Wednesday, the 28th of that month.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Bryce.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
